      value_type: 'Fair Market Value — per IRS definition (Treas. Reg. §25.2512-1). The FMV must reflect the property \'as is\' including ALL encumbrances and conditions: the historic preservation easement, the boundary dispute, the environmental REC, and the existing mortgage. Important: For gift tax purposes when a life estate is retained, the IRS includes the full FMV of the property in the gift calculation (similar to IRC §2036 for estates), and the remaining mortgage may offset the gift value (net gift), but this is a tax/legal calculation, not an appraisal issue. The appraiser values the property; the tax professional calculates the taxable gift.',
      effective_date: 'The date of the gift transfer to the trust — the appraiser must coordinate with the attorney on the anticipated transfer date. The appraisal must be completed within the IRS timing requirements.',
